Morphology and variability . In the abundant material that I have studied, the overall colouration of
Anthaxia ( H. ) wethloi
varies from dark bronze to bright coppery (
Figs. 92–94
), sometimes with a slight reddish or greenish shade, regardless of sex. Sexual dichromatism is virtually absent, except for a bright green tinge present on the frons of some males (
Fig. 37
). Females also differ from males by having a more stout body, wider frons (
Fig. 38
), less incurved meso- and metatibiae, and a deep notch on the anal ventrite (
Fig. 65
). The shape of the anal notch is rather variable except that it is always rather deep, it can be narrowly shaped, widely rounded or widely parallel. Males may also very rarely have a slight indication of an apical notch.
